      "citation_count": 1,
      "final_answer_text": "The programming-workflow zettel characterizes the actual day-to-day skill of programming as an iterative cycle centered on debugging. This core skill involves a methodical problem-solving approach that relies heavily on searching for and applying existing solutions to diagnose and fix errors using external resources. It is explicitly NOT rapid, flawless typing, nor is it primarily about typing speed."
