      "citation_grounding": 1.0,
      "answer_correctness_proxy": 0.19444444444444445,
      "ragas_proxy_score": 0.9375,
      "overall_strength": 0.6000000000000001,
      "refusal": false,
      "cited_node_ids": [
        "nl-the-pragmatic-engineer-t"
      ],
      "citation_count": 7,
      "final_answer_text": "The Pragmatic Engineer newsletter defines a 'product-minded' engineer as someone who possesses product-thinking skills and user empathy. These engineers actively cultivate product-mindedness by consistently asking 'why', utilizing scenarios, engaging directly with customer support, and proactively assisting Product Managers with use cases. They also join customer calls to gain direct user insights and leverage AI tools to aggregate user signals from internal communication and project management platforms. An exemplary product-minded engineer embodies these principles. This approach differs from a stereotypical implementation-focused engineer by expanding beyond just coding to encompass a deep understanding of the product's purpose, user needs, and overall business value, even designing elements like error messages for distinct audiences (human users and AI agents) as a primary product interface."
    },
